This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to summarize spoken meetings. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses both unsupervised and supervised learning frameworks, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves clustering and topic modeling, which are techniques commonly used in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Software Development (cs.SD), respectively. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant to this paper.
